The paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of computer science that studies decision-making processes involving multiple agents. The paper specifically focuses on a general model of social choice called Sub-Committee Voting (SCV), which is a topic that falls under the category of computational game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes extensions of the justified representation axioms for proportional representation in approval-based committee voting, which involves algorithms and optimization techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The analysis of the properties and relations of these axioms involves mathematical proofs and complexity analysis, which are topics that fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
